Nakuru residents are a fearful lot especially during this festive season. This is due to the existence of marauding youths who raid and rob homes, business premises and taxi drivers. Residents who spoke to KTN news paint a picture of a merciless and daring gang and suspect the outlawed 'confirm' criminal gang could be regrouping. Nakuru police commander Stephen Matu has however downplayed the possibility of the gang's resurgence and called on residents to volunteer crucial information to the authorities.